cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.ST, cs.SY, cs.NA. 

The paper deals with parameter estimation under constraints, which is a common problem in information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), statistics (cs.ST), control systems (cs.SY), and numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper proposes a new definition for unbiasedness under constraints and derives a Cramér-Rao-type bound on the mean-squared-error of such estimators. These topics are relevant to all of the above sub-categories.
